<br>
All of our items now have slots for augmentation.  The items you can buy from the LDON Adventure Merchants usually have MORE than one augmentation slot!<br>
<br>
After you decide, take the item and augmentation and go to one of the Wayfarer camps.  Look for the bird bath looking thingie, click it like it's a forge or pottery wheel, put the two inside and hit combine.  Voila!<br>
<br>
I've won two of them... one for +6 poison and another for +6 intelligence, but I hadn't done anything with them because I figured those choices were going to take a lot of thought.  However, I just learned this weekend that you can REVERSE your augmentation choice by buying a &quot;solvent&quot; from the Magus guys!  Woohoo!<br>
<br>
Mugo did a really cool thing and bought a  neck item from them and augmented it with Regeneration I.  There are also weapon proc's and focus enhancements available as your points build!  <br>
<br>
Pretty neat, but I'm saving for my upper level disarm trap spells.   <p>Sytox 63 Warlock<br>
